  "prompt": "How can I sleep in noise?",
  "response": "Here are some tips to help you sleep in a noisy environment:\n\n1. Use earplugs\n- Foam or silicone earplugs can block out significant noise\n- Choose comfortable, high-noise reduction rating (NRR) plugs\n\n2. Noise-canceling headphones or earbuds\n- Active noise cancellation can reduce background sounds\n- Some are specifically designed for sleeping\n\n3. White noise machines\n- Generate consistent background sounds that mask other noises\n- Can include sounds like rain, fan, or static\n\n4. Smartphone apps\n- Many free apps offer white noise or ambient sound options\n- Can be used with or without headphones\n\n5. Fan or air purifier\n- Creates constant background noise\n- Can help drown out intermittent sounds\n\n6. Sound-blocking curtains\n- Heavy, thick curtains can reduce outside noise\n- Helps insulate your sleeping area\n\n7. Rearrange your bedroom\n- Move bed away from noise sources\n- Use furniture or wall hangings to absorb sound\n\n8. Relaxation techniques\n- Practice meditation or deep breathing\n- Can help you stay calm and less reactive to noise\n\n9. Get used to the noise gradually\n- Expose yourself to sounds in controlled amounts\n- Can help build tolerance over time",
